Welcome, have you been here before?
Continue

Thanks for coming. This is a shared public space where we can collectively reflect on our inner worlds and feelings through the pandemic.

Please answer a few questions before you enter...
Yes
No
Did you, or someone you know, lose a loved one during the pandemic?
Next
This lantern symbolizes the light of their soul. You may see other lanterns around the tree. They are put there by fellow visitors like you, in remembrance of the departed.
Done

Times have been difficult for those who are suffering.

Make a wish (in your mind). It could be for yourself, for a friend or family, or even a stranger.

The wish will bloom as a flower on the frozen lake.
ENTER

Our souls are represented as butterflies in this space. 

If you see other butterflies, be kind to them. They are other people like you from around the world.

And enjoy your visit.
ENTER

Good to see you again. 

Enjoy your visit!
